-- German Court Orders Museum to Return Nazi-Looted Posters to Heir
-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   H i c k l e y
-- 2012-03-16T08:18:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/german-court-orders-museum-to-return-nazi-looted-posters-to-heir.html
A German court ordered Berlin’s
Deutsches Historisches Museum to return a collection of 4,259
posters looted by the Gestapo to the son of Hans Sachs, a Jewish
dentist who fled Nazi  Germany , Sachs’s lawyer said.  “We won on all counts,” Matthias Druba of FPS
Rechtsanwaelte, Sachs’s Berlin lawyer, said in an e-mail today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Catherine Hickley at 
 chickley@bloomberg.net  